          "kind": "fail",
          "level": "error",
          "rank": 92.5,
          "message": {
            "text": "The 'command' parameter flows unsanitized from the 'execute_job' API handler to subprocess.run(shell=True), enabling arbitrary command execution.",
            "markdown": "## Command Injection via API Handler Parameter\n\n**Rule:** `CWE-78/api-handler` · **Severity:** Error · **Rank:** 92.5\n\n### What's Wrong\n\nThe `command` parameter at `src/handler.py:38` is passed directly to `subprocess.run()` with `shell=True` at line 42, with no validation.\n\n### Evidence\n```python\ndef execute_job(request):\n    command = request.json['command']  # untrusted input\n    result = subprocess.run(command, shell=True, capture_output=True)  # injection sink\n```\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Start the server: `python src/server.py`\n2. Run: `curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/execute -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{\"command\": \"id\"}'`\n3. Observe: server executes injected command and returns output.\n\n### Recommended Fix\n```python\nALLOWED_COMMANDS = {'status', 'health', 'version'}\ncommand = request.json.get('command', '')\nif command not in ALLOWED_COMMANDS:\n    abort(400, 'Invalid command')\nresult = subprocess.run(['/usr/bin/mytool', command], shell=False, capture_output=True)\n```\n\n### References\n- [CWE-78](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/78.html)"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/handler.py",
                  "uriBaseId": "SRCROOT",
                  "index": 0
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 42,
                  "startColumn": 5,
                  "endLine": 42,
                  "endColumn": 86,
                  "snippet": {
                    "text": "    result = subprocess.run(command, shell=True, capture_output=True, timeout=timeout)"
                  }
                }
              },
              "logicalLocations": [
                {
                  "name": "execute_job",
                  "fullyQualifiedName": "handler::execute_job",
                  "kind": "function"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": { "text": "Allowlist valid commands and disable shell=True" },
              "artifactChanges": [
                {
                  "artifactLocation": { "uri": "src/handler.py", "uriBaseId": "SRCROOT" },
                  "replacements": [
